1. Convert equilibrated CHARMM structure to LAMMPS format
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   cd chm2lmp

   perl charmm2lammps.pl all36_msevb ls2 48.413 48.413 77.868 -cmap > chm2lmp.log

   cd ..
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Inputs:  charmm2lammps.pl
            top_all36_msevb.rtf
            par_all36_msevb.par
            ls2.psf
            ls2.crd (ls2.pdb will be used if without ls2.crd)

   Outputs: ls2_ctrl.psf
            ls2_ctrl.pdb
            ls2.data
            ls2.in

2. Update LAMMPS *.data
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   cp chm2lmp/ls2.data .

   Update following sections in ls2.data:
     1) Bond Coeffs section (especially reactive O-H bonds)
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. Prepare evb.top
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   1st column: atom number


   2nd column: index of a reactive molecule/residue defined in evb.cfg

               1 --> hydronium,	H3O
               2 --> water,	H2O


   3rd column: index of atoms in a reactive molecule/residue defined in evb_single.par


   E.g., for hydronium here,
         1) in ls2.data, the "Atoms" section
               19110    3022    37     -0.32          0.50708          0.11013          8.96698  # OTH
               19111    3022    36      0.44          0.01619         -0.72586          8.86028  # HTH
               19112    3022    36      0.44          0.09617           0.8353          8.46567  # HTH
               19113    3022    36      0.44          0.52963          0.31943          9.90094  # HTH

         2) in evb.cfg
            settype H3O 1 : hydronium

         3) in evb_single.par
            [molecule_type.start.H3O]

            :      HO        2
            :      |         |
            :      OH        1
            :     / \       / \
            :   HO   HO    3   4

            : number of atoms,   bonds,   angles,  dihedrals,   impropers,   starting rc
                          4        3        3         0           0          1
            : atomic information
            : atom type   charge   kernel
              OH          -0.32     1
              HO           0.44     1
              HO           0.44     1
              HO           0.44     1

         4) in evb.top
            19110 1 1
            19111 1 2
            19112 1 3
            19113 1 4
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4. Prepare evb.type
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Atom/Bond/Angle/Dihedral/Improper   "names"     should match those defined in evb_single.par
   Atom/Bond/Angle/Dihedral/Improper   "indeces"   should match those defined in ls2.data

   E.g., for hydronium here,
         1) in evb.type
            : Atom Type
            #define HO 36
            #define OH 37

            : Bond Type
            #define OH-HO 39

            : Angle Type
            #define HO-OH-HO 73

         2) in evb_single.par
            [molecule_type.start.H3O]

            :      HO        2
            :      |         |
            :      OH        1
            :     / \       / \
            :   HO   HO    3   4

            : number of atoms,   bonds,   angles,  dihedrals,   impropers,   starting rc
                          4        3        3         0           0          1
            : atomic information
            : atom type   charge   kernel
              OH          -0.32     1
              HO           0.44     1
              HO           0.44     1
              HO           0.44     1
            : bonds
            :  atom 1       atom 2      type
               1            2           OH-HO
               1            3           OH-HO
               1            4           OH-HO
            : angles
            :  atom 1       atom 2       atom 3     type
               2            1            3          HO-OH-HO
               2            1            4          HO-OH-HO
               3            1            4          HO-OH-HO

            : COC
            4
            1 2 3 4

            [molecule_type.end]

         3) in ls2.data
            Masses
                  36      1.008  # HTH
                  37    15.9994  # OTH

            Bond Coeffs # hybrid
                  39      morse           79.086356      2.083387      0.98  # HTH  OTH

            Angle Coeffs # charmm
                  73         38.74335         111.7269                0                0  # HTH  OTH  HTH
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------

5. Run MS-RMD simulations
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   sbatch msrmd.qsub

   Update "set stage = 1    # current stage" line to continue the simulation
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
